Hello, I have cloned [JRA-43658|https://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRA-43658] since this is still reproducible on 7.0.5, 7.0.9 and 7.0.10.

h3. Summary
Regardless of the context path setup for JIRA, accessing the *Release Notes* link from a version's details page builds a URL with context path {{/jira}}, which possibly results in a 404 error.

h3. Steps to Reproduce

# Setup a context path different than {{/jira}} for your JIRA instance;
# On a Scrum board, expand the *Versions* sidebar, then expand one of the versions and click *Details*;
# Click *Release Notes*, just below the version's name;
# Notice the URL built uses {{/jira}} for its context path, which results either on a blank page or a 404 error;

h3. Expected Behavior
The context path should be retrieved from the application's Base URL, and not hard-coded.

h3. Actual Behavior
Every time the URL for Release Notes is built, the context path is set to {{/jira}}.

h3.Workaround
h5. Option 1
You can manually edit the URL from your web browser, adding the right context path (as shown in screenshot below).
!Screen Shot 2015-06-02 at 11.42.40 AM.png|thumbnail!

h5. Option 2
Add the following script in JIRA's [Announcement Banner|https://confluence.atlassian.com/jira/configuring-an-announcement-banner-185729633.html]
{code}
<script type="text/javascript">
jQuery(window).load(function(){
	release_report_notes_link = document.getElementById("release-report-notes-link")
	if (release_report_notes_link != null){
		release_report_notes_link.setAttribute("href",release_report_notes_link.getAttribute("href").replace('/jira', AJS.contextPath()));
	}
});
</script>
{code}

